## Build

```bash
cmake --preset debug
cmake --build --preset debug
```

The generated `CMakePresets.json` and `CMakeLists.txt` already point at:

- device tuple: `{{ vendor }}/{{ family }}/{{ device }}` (arch `{{ arch }}`)
- `ALLOY_ROOT={{ alloy_root }}`{% if toolchain_bin %}
- toolchain bin: `{{ toolchain_bin }}`{% endif %}

## Customise the board

`board/board_config.hpp` declares pin assignments and peripheral choices for your
hardware. Edit it whenever you change the wiring; see the in-tree boards inside
`{{ alloy_root }}/boards/` for reference shapes.

## Flash and monitor

`alloy flash` and `alloy monitor` work once the SDK is installed and the toolchain is on
PATH:

```bash
alloy flash --board custom --target {{ project }} --build-first
alloy monitor --board custom
```

## VS Code

Open this directory in VS Code. `.vscode/settings.json` configures clangd against
`build/debug/compile_commands.json`; `tasks.json` exposes build/flash/monitor;
`launch.json` provides a debug configuration when a probe is available.
